# Biography

Andres Ladino is a postdoctoral researcher in Automatic Control at the [IFSTTAR](http://www.ifsttar.fr/en/welcome/) Laboratory. His recent research interests include networked control systems, intelligent transportation systems and artificial intelligence. He works at [LICIT](http://www.licit.ifsttar.fr) group, which develops traffic flow theory, and traffic simulation.

He is also passioned about the Data Science community and the recent work developed around reproducible research. Fan of [#rstats](https://twitter.com/search?q=%23rstats&src=typd). 
